				Prière du soir; 4. Nostalgie; 5. Nocturne.</i></font></p>
				<p style="text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in;" class="MsoNormal" align="left">
				<span style="font-size: 12pt;"><font face="Verdana" size="2">
				----- for piano, violin, viola &amp; cello.<span style>&nbsp; </span>New 
				York: Carl Fischer.</font></span></p>
				<p style="text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in;" class="MsoNormal" align="left">
				<font face="Verdana" size="2"><b style><i>----- 1. Melida; A 
				Creole tropical dance</i></b>, for orchestra, arr. by Charles J. 
				Roberts.<span style>&nbsp; </span>New York: Carl Fischer, 1927.<span style>&nbsp;
				</span>5p. (piano score)<span style>&nbsp; </span>(#<i>24318</i>).</font></p>
				<p style="text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in;" class="MsoNormal" align="left">
				<font face="Verdana" size="2"><b style><i>----- 2. Isma-o; The 
				echo</i></b>, for piano.<span style>&nbsp; </span>New York: G. 
				Schirmer.<span style>&nbsp; </span>Library: Spingarn.</font></p>
				<p style="text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in;" class="MsoNormal" align="left">
				<span style="font-size: 12pt;"><font face="Verdana" size="2">
				----- CD: Jean Ernst Saint-Éloi, guitar, MIDI realised.<span style>&nbsp;
				</span>(1999; <i style>Music of the Haitian masters, vol. 1</i>).</font></span></p>
				<p style="text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in;" class="MsoNormal" align="left">
				<font face="Verdana" size="2"><b style><i>----- 3. Prière du 
